<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-12T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="1673" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1673">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">125.267/8–1249: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Clark</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Canton</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-12T19:00:00-04:00">August 12,
                                1949—7 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>TelCan 557. Re first para telCan 553, Aug 12, entire ConGen Canton shld be
                        closed whenever in ur and Rankin’s judgment this move desirable prior
                        arrival Commie forces. Make all necessary preparations <pb facs="1324" n="1314" xml:id="pg_1314"/> departure personnel who shld proceed first
                        to Hóng Kong. Administrative instructions re closure and future assignment
                        departees, including Rankin, will be subject sep tel. Pls make necessary
                        notification Amer natls.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>